This is the code I created to enable the bme280 sensor to be used in openmote-b using contiki-ng os.
However, in order to use these codes, you need to modify some of the contiki-ng files. The parts that need to be corrected will be explained below.

What needs to be modified
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
contiki-ng/arch/dev/sensor/bme280/bme280.h

55 #define BME280_ADDR              (0x77 << 1) /* Alternative 0x76 */
The upper part should be changed as shown below.
55 #define BME280_ADDR              (0x76)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
contiki-ng/arch/platform/openmote/openmote-b/board.h

181 #define I2C_SCL_PORT             GPIO_B_NUM
182 #define I2C_SCL_PIN              5
183 #define I2C_SDA_PORT             GPIO_B_NUM
184 #define I2C_SDA_PIN              4

The upper part should be changed as shown below.

181 #define I2C_SCL_PORT             GPIO_B_NUM
182 #define I2C_SCL_PIN              1
183 #define I2C_SDA_PORT             GPIO_B_NUM
184 #define I2C_SDA_PIN              0
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------



This is a phrase for flashing on the openmote-b board.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
sudo make TARGET=openmote BOARD=openmote-b PORT=/dev/ttyUSB3 sensor-test.upload
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
